# Loot and scan output are engagement artifacts, not source. Track them
# deliberately (git add -f) rather than by default — they routinely contain
# credentials, and this repo is a scratch pad, not a vault.
loot/*
scans/*
.direnv/

# Keep the directories themselves — both in this template (or `nix flake init`
# would scaffold an engagement missing two of its five dirs) and in a live
# engagement, where an empty scans/ is still where scans go.
!loot/.gitkeep
!scans/.gitkeep
